    "id": "cdx_ig_46_hazard",
    "description": "CDX.NA.IG.46 index hazard curve calibrated from index par-spread quotes, chained on a USD-OIS discount curve bootstrapped from deposit and IRS quotes in the same plan. Step 1 produces the USD-OIS discount curve; step 2 calibrates the CDX hazard curve against it. The envelope is fully self-bootstrapping from quotes \u2014 no hand-entered curves in initial_market. Differs from 03_single_name_hazard.json by switching the entity from a single-name issuer to the index name, with index-shaped spreads (50/75/100/110/120 bp). The HazardCurveParams schema does not currently expose an IMM-date convention flag (that flag exists only on BaseCorrelationParams); pillars are tenor-based for both single-name and index calibrations, and the IMM rolling shows up only inside the synthetic CDS schedule generation controlled by doc_clause. doc_clause `isda_na` is the USD default and applies to both single-name and index NA conventions. Used as reference for 05 (base correlation) and 06 (CDX index vol).",
